%N A397323 a(1) = 1; for n > 1, a(n) is the smallest unused number placed on a hexagon spiral that has a common factor with any earlier term that is adjacent to it on the spiral.
%C A397323 A variation of A397218 and A354434 on a hexagonal spiral.
%C A397323 It is conjectured that all positive numbers appear.
%H A397323 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A397323/b397323.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000</a>
%H A397323 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A397323/a397323.png">Image of the first 1000 terms on the hexagonal spiral</a>. The number colors are graduated across the spectrum, from red to violet, to show their relative size. Small grey lines show the direction of the spiral.
%H A397323 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A397323/a397323_1.png">Image of the first 50000 terms on the hexagonal spiral showing their relative size</a>. Even terms are also surrounded with a white border.
%e A397323 The spiral begins:
%e A397323 .
%e A397323             25--80--68--66--64
%e A397323            /                  \
%e A397323          55   5---40--38--36   62
%e A397323         /    /              \    \
%e A397323       75   35   15--18--16   34   58
%e A397323      /    /    /          \    \    \
%e A397323    51   42   21   6---4    14   32   70
%e A397323   /    /    /    /      \    \    \    \
%e A397323  57  39   24    3    1---2   10   28    7
%e A397323   \    \    \    \          /    /    /
%e A397323    63   45   27    9--12---8   26   56
%e A397323      \    \    \              /    /
%e A397323       69   48   30--33--22--20   52   .
%e A397323         \    \                  /    .
%e A397323          72   44--54--60--46--50    .
%e A397323            \                       /
%e A397323             74--76--78--82--84--86
%e A397323 .
%e A397323 a(14) = 21 as when a(14) is placed its existing adjacent terms are 3, 6 and 15, and 21 is the smallest unused number that has a common factor with 3, 6 and 15.
%Y A397323 Cf. A396357 (start 2), A397218, A354434, A064413.
